WEBVTT

00:39.790 --> 00:41.692
[SHIP'S ENGINE RUMBLING]

00:41.692 --> 00:41.792
[SHIP'S ENGINE RUMBLING]

00:48.591 --> 00:50.217
[HULL CREAKING]

00:57.183 --> 00:58.684
ZERO: How's the wound, B?

00:59.268 --> 01:00.936
BRANDON: I gotta get off my feet.

01:05.858 --> 01:07.193
[IN SPANISH] Welcome aboard.

01:07.818 --> 01:09.737
We're happy to be going back.

01:10.237 --> 01:12.531
By chance, do you have any snacks?

01:13.866 --> 01:15.201
Ah.

01:15.284 --> 01:17.495
Seriously... Do you have First Aid?

01:17.578 --> 01:19.330
He has a bad wound.

01:21.957 --> 01:23.459
How about a place to rest?

01:24.210 --> 01:25.711
[GROANS SOFTLY]

01:25.795 --> 01:27.046
[CHUCKLES]

01:28.047 --> 01:29.423
[IN ENGLISH] No? Okay.

01:30.633 --> 01:31.634
[IN SPANISH] Hello.

01:31.717 --> 01:33.719
[WIND HOWLING]

01:39.892 --> 01:42.102
[WIND HOWLING]

01:46.941 --> 01:48.234
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

01:48.317 --> 01:49.693
[IN ENGLISH] Uh, Zero. We--

01:49.777 --> 01:51.403
[GUNS COCKING]

01:56.075 --> 01:57.576
G.R.I.T. terrorists.

01:57.660 --> 01:59.703
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

02:04.792 --> 02:05.751
[GRUNTS]

02:05.835 --> 02:07.920
[ALL GRUNTING]

02:10.297 --> 02:11.966
[GUNSHOTS]

02:13.467 --> 02:14.301
[GROANS]

02:20.307 --> 02:22.184
MAN: [OVER RADIO] <c.s0>Enroute.
Do you copy?

02:25.312 --> 02:26.814
<c.s0>Do you copy?

02:26.897 --> 02:28.315
[BOAT ENGINES APPROACHING]

02:28.983 --> 02:30.359
[IN ENGLISH] Oh, that can't be good.

02:30.442 --> 02:32.528
If you don't copy... Go with God!

02:32.611 --> 02:34.238
[STRAINING]

02:34.321 --> 02:35.948
Who the hell is coming?

02:36.031 --> 02:36.949
Death.

02:37.032 --> 02:39.451
Courtesy of Roman Díaz.

02:47.668 --> 02:49.128
[MAN 2 YELLING IN SPANISH]

02:52.256 --> 02:55.009
[GRUNTS, GROANS SOFTLY]

02:56.844 --> 02:58.095
[IN ENGLISH] Shit!

02:58.971 --> 03:00.472
I can't see a damn thing.

03:00.556 --> 03:01.640
[GUNSHOTS]

03:11.775 --> 03:12.776
[GRUNTS]

03:20.618 --> 03:22.202
[PANTING]

03:22.953 --> 03:24.622
[GROANS]

03:39.219 --> 03:40.596
[GUN COCKS]

03:43.349 --> 03:45.059
[GROANING IN PAIN]

03:51.148 --> 03:53.567
[BULLETS RICOCHETING]

03:57.905 --> 04:01.075
[SIGHS, BREATHING PAINFULLY]

04:03.786 --> 04:06.538
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

04:10.417 --> 04:12.294
[HEART THUMPING]

04:12.378 --> 04:14.254
[CHAINS RATTLING]

04:28.060 --> 04:29.436
[WATER GURGLING]

04:31.230 --> 04:32.898
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

04:32.982 --> 04:34.108
[GUN FIRES]

04:39.238 --> 04:40.406
[GUN COCKS]

04:44.284 --> 04:46.495
[GUNSHOTS]

04:46.578 --> 04:47.538
[BRANDON GROANS]

04:48.831 --> 04:50.082
That's a lot of blood, B.

04:50.165 --> 04:53.043
Can we get a break, please? Come on!

04:53.127 --> 04:54.962
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

04:55.045 --> 04:57.047
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

05:04.638 --> 05:07.599
[MAN 4 URGING IN SPANISH]

05:09.226 --> 05:10.060
[CLACKS]

05:11.186 --> 05:12.354
[GUN FIRES]

05:12.438 --> 05:13.605
[SCREAMS]

05:18.485 --> 05:19.862
Ready to fire.

05:20.654 --> 05:21.655
Let it fly!

05:23.532 --> 05:25.409
[FLARE CRACKLING]

05:26.118 --> 05:27.244
[GUN FIRES]

05:28.162 --> 05:29.538
[PANICKED SHOUTING]

05:29.621 --> 05:30.706
[EXPLOSION]

05:31.206 --> 05:33.000
Yeah! Hell of a shot, B!

05:36.086 --> 05:37.421
Yes!

05:37.504 --> 05:38.672
[EARS RINGING]

05:42.426 --> 05:43.719
[RAPID HEARTBEAT]

05:43.802 --> 05:44.803
[ECHOING] B?

05:49.933 --> 05:50.934
Come on.

05:52.436 --> 05:53.437
Shit!

05:54.730 --> 05:55.981
Hey.

05:56.065 --> 05:57.149
Hang in there.

06:02.488 --> 06:04.490
[WHIRRING INTENSIFIES]

06:04.573 --> 06:06.825
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

06:22.925 --> 06:24.426
INTERROGATOR: Ezekiel Rosenberg.

06:25.344 --> 06:26.762
You have exactly five minutes

06:34.853 --> 06:36.355
to assist on an assignment.

06:36.438 --> 06:37.523
We took losses.

06:39.691 --> 06:40.734
Many losses.

06:47.616 --> 06:49.284
The information we gathered could--

06:49.368 --> 06:50.869
INTERROGATOR: Where is Brandon Beckett?

06:52.454 --> 06:53.831
Is he still alive?

07:01.296 --> 07:02.297
INTERROGATOR: Snags?

07:03.257 --> 07:06.301
Your specificity, it's, uh... inspiring.

07:07.219 --> 07:09.179
What the hell happened out there?

07:17.312 --> 07:19.148
It took Brandon somewhere safe.

07:23.318 --> 07:25.571
Then I got an encrypted text,

07:31.910 --> 07:35.664
Your turn. What the hell am I doing here?

07:50.512 --> 07:51.847
Let's bring you up to speed.

08:02.524 --> 08:04.651
You know, saying that the United States

08:18.415 --> 08:21.084
Just nod... if you're still with me.

08:28.467 --> 08:29.968
has been wiped from the planet.

08:31.053 --> 08:33.263
G.R.I.T. is no more.

08:36.308 --> 08:38.352
But here's the snag, Ezekiel.

08:39.770 --> 08:41.021
Your team is on the run.

08:41.647 --> 08:42.648
They're in hiding.

08:48.111 --> 08:50.280
Peter Stolnitz, aka Intel Pete,

08:56.203 --> 08:57.871
since the Costa Verde snafu.

08:59.373 --> 09:00.374
It's just you.

09:06.296 --> 09:07.589
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

09:09.174 --> 09:12.511
Last chance. Where is Brandon Beckett?

09:17.808 --> 09:18.892
[DOOR OPENS]

09:24.731 --> 09:27.192
Patriot Act? That's for terrorists.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.447
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

09:32.531 --> 09:35.200
[BREATH SHUDDERING]

09:53.093 --> 09:54.511
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

10:00.017 --> 10:01.601
[GRUNTS]

10:03.395 --> 10:04.521
MAN: Hello, Zero.

10:07.107 --> 10:08.108
Where's my son?

10:08.650 --> 10:10.652
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

10:14.114 --> 10:15.324
My fellow Costa Verdians.

10:21.538 --> 10:25.542
<c.s0>illegally entered Costa Verde
and killed a government contractor,

10:25.625 --> 10:28.754
<c.s0>along with over 100 soldiers.

10:37.846 --> 10:40.390
The United States completely denies

10:47.814 --> 10:50.275
<c.s0>was assassinated
by a sniper hired by Americans.

10:55.155 --> 10:58.408
REPORTER: <c.s0>And wasn't American Marine
Brandon Beckett a suspect?

10:58.492 --> 11:01.036
FRED: <c.s0>No, Brandon Beckett
did not kill Bruno Díaz.

11:03.789 --> 11:05.874
<c.s0>thanks in part to him
and his father Thomas Beckett.

11:08.585 --> 11:10.087
MICHAELS: <c.s0>It's not the first time

11:10.170 --> 11:12.130
<c.s0>Costa Verde has tried
to distract the world

11:12.214 --> 11:14.132
<c.s0>from the poverty, the corruption,

11:14.216 --> 11:16.802
<c.s0>the brutality taking place
within its borders.

11:20.555 --> 11:24.601
<c.s0>to meddle in and control
our domestic affairs.

11:24.684 --> 11:28.271
REPORTER: <c.s0>Bottom line, the Americans
are helping these so-called Phoenix Rebels

11:28.355 --> 11:30.982
<c.s0>to cause disruption in Costa Verde.

11:31.066 --> 11:34.027
We cannot allow this any longer!

11:34.111 --> 11:37.823
<c.s0>Their violence will spill across
the border and onto Tierra Nuevan streets.

11:37.906 --> 11:39.282
MICHAELS: <c.s0>As for G.R.I.T.,

11:39.366 --> 11:42.327
<c.s0>the Global Response and Intelligence Team

11:45.497 --> 11:49.793
<c.s0>Anyone involved in this terrorist
false flag organization

11:49.876 --> 11:53.922
<c.s0>will be hunted down and will face
the consequences for this operation.

11:54.005 --> 11:55.882
Be warned, America.

11:55.966 --> 11:59.594
You will answer for this treachery!

12:00.887 --> 12:02.055
<c.s0>Gracias.

12:09.396 --> 12:10.897
[CREW GROANS]

12:10.981 --> 12:11.982
Stupid.

12:14.609 --> 12:16.319
[GROANS] Come on, man!

12:21.491 --> 12:22.868
[CREW CHEERS]

12:26.538 --> 12:27.622
[GROANS]

12:29.791 --> 12:32.210
Listen. Listen.

12:37.966 --> 12:40.510
CABRERA: [OVER PHONE] <c.s0>The Prime Minister's
Navy Squad failed to prevent Beckett

12:40.594 --> 12:42.971
<c.s0>-and G.R.I.T. from escaping the country.

12:45.015 --> 12:46.057
Father or son?

12:46.141 --> 12:47.392
[GUN PARTS CLANKING]

12:49.603 --> 12:51.021
[LAUGHTER]

12:55.525 --> 12:57.819
<c.s0>-an enemy of the son.
-

13:05.911 --> 13:09.164
KRUGER: <c.s0>Oh, yeah. Your boss wants
to use him as a political chess piece.

13:17.797 --> 13:19.216
so they will not be there.

13:19.925 --> 13:23.678
KRUGER: <c.s0>No shit.
That's why we're starting in Costa Verde.

13:25.931 --> 13:27.182
You're coming here?

13:39.277 --> 13:41.238
Which will bring Brandon to us.

13:41.321 --> 13:42.989
KRUGER: <c.s0>Killing a Beckett's gonna be fun.

13:43.073 --> 13:45.242
<c.s0>And you had better
make sure my cash is ready.

13:45.992 --> 13:47.202
Of course.

13:47.285 --> 13:49.246
We have a crypto account set up for this--

13:54.000 --> 13:55.669
I want real money. I want cash.

13:58.713 --> 13:59.714
Don't worry.

14:00.215 --> 14:01.132
[CLICKS]

14:01.925 --> 14:03.260
You will get your money.

14:06.680 --> 14:07.973
And if you don't pay...

14:12.269 --> 14:15.188
Call me when it's done.

14:15.272 --> 14:16.773
[CREW CHEERING]

14:21.903 --> 14:25.240
[DEEP BREATHING]

14:27.284 --> 14:29.411
INTEL PETE: [OVER PHONE] <c.s0>Roman's got
the entire country of Costa Verde

14:29.494 --> 14:30.579
<c.s0>on a media blackout.

14:30.662 --> 14:32.747
<c.s0>No real news
or social media gets in or out.

14:32.831 --> 14:35.584
<c.s0>But it looks like some rebels
have been able to occasionally break down

14:35.667 --> 14:37.919
<c.s0>the firewalls and spread the truth.

14:38.003 --> 14:40.964
<c.s0>There's actually some pretty great
Roman Díaz memes going around.

14:41.047 --> 14:43.383
<c.s0>There's this one with a cat,
a can opener and--

14:43.466 --> 14:45.010
[CHUCKLES] <c.s0>...you just gotta see it.

14:53.560 --> 14:55.145
[INTEL PETE SLURPING DRINK]

14:59.482 --> 15:01.818
<c.s0>He doesn't really
strike me as a family man.

15:09.451 --> 15:10.827
is gonna be executed.

15:15.248 --> 15:18.084
<c.s0>I'm getting close.
You should have an update in a few hours.

15:19.294 --> 15:20.962
If anyone can do it, you can, Pete.

15:21.921 --> 15:25.342
<c.s0>Brandon, listen. If you need help,
say the word. We'll be there.

15:37.562 --> 15:40.273
She'd be literally hunted by everyone.

15:44.944 --> 15:46.946
-<c.s0>Okay.

15:47.030 --> 15:49.449
[MUFFLED CHATTER IN SPANISH]

15:51.117 --> 15:52.410
[IN ENGLISH] Hey, I gotta run.

15:53.244 --> 15:54.871
Be careful.

15:54.954 --> 15:57.165
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

16:02.796 --> 16:04.422
[DOOR OPENS]

16:04.506 --> 16:05.924
ZERO: "Thunderstorm's coming."

16:06.007 --> 16:07.008
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

16:09.844 --> 16:11.805
"...and go dancing in the rain."

16:23.441 --> 16:24.442
THOMAS: Hmm.

16:26.361 --> 16:27.487
FROST: Devon Frost.

16:30.365 --> 16:32.075
when we were sent to Costa Verde.

16:33.618 --> 16:35.245
It is a pleasure to meet you, sir.

16:35.995 --> 16:37.539
He's a keeper, this one.

16:51.511 --> 16:52.512
What?

16:53.430 --> 16:55.223
[DRAMATIC MUSICAL STING]

16:58.184 --> 16:59.352
[SIGHS WEARILY]

17:00.687 --> 17:01.938
So we can't go home?

17:10.613 --> 17:13.116
The President and the State Department

17:17.787 --> 17:19.205
You've seen this before.

17:20.165 --> 17:21.499
You know how it works.

17:21.583 --> 17:22.834
[BRANDON SIGHS]

17:31.885 --> 17:33.261
This whole base was the rally point?

17:33.344 --> 17:35.138
ZERO: Yeah. This is where we were supposed

17:38.725 --> 17:39.726
THOMAS: You know what?

17:40.226 --> 17:41.227
You should leave.

17:47.859 --> 17:48.902
FROST: Roman won't invade.

18:03.875 --> 18:06.085
[BRANDON SCOFFS, INHALES DEEPLY]

18:06.169 --> 18:08.087
So what the hell do you suggest I do?

18:08.171 --> 18:09.172
ZERO: We fight.

18:09.923 --> 18:10.924
We fight.

18:11.466 --> 18:12.717
Like we always do, B.

18:17.138 --> 18:18.723
Zero, tap the brakes.

18:19.182 --> 18:20.725
There's no country backing you.

18:25.146 --> 18:26.397
THOMAS: Oh, for Christ's sake,

18:30.318 --> 18:31.361
You know what you need to do?

18:38.368 --> 18:39.828
It's your call, B.

18:42.038 --> 18:43.039
[BRANDON SIGHS]

18:48.127 --> 18:50.630
but without going into their country.

18:56.135 --> 18:57.178
They win, we win.

18:57.262 --> 18:58.680
That's a lot of "ifs."

19:05.103 --> 19:06.604
<c.s0>How did you guys find us?

19:10.692 --> 19:12.819
Tell us what's going on in Costa Verde.

19:16.948 --> 19:18.283
along the Tierra Nueva border.

19:18.992 --> 19:21.578
<c.s0>I've orchestrated a squad to investigate.

19:26.040 --> 19:29.210
<c.s0>And when you all get here,
there'll be no stopping us.

19:30.461 --> 19:31.629
[BRANDON SIGHS]

19:33.631 --> 19:35.341
We can't come back to Costa Verde, Zondi.

19:41.306 --> 19:43.141
to create an international incident.

20:07.165 --> 20:09.667
<c.s0>We don't need your MREs and toilet paper.

20:11.669 --> 20:13.504
<c.s0>We need soldiers!

20:13.588 --> 20:16.591
<c.s0>We need the best sniper
in the world fighting by our side.

20:16.674 --> 20:17.800
[SIGHS]

20:24.891 --> 20:27.268
that is being brought to us as we speak.

20:27.352 --> 20:28.561
[SIGHS IMPATIENTLY]

20:29.646 --> 20:32.482
<c.s0>They're bringing us weapons
to fight this battle on our own.

20:33.441 --> 20:35.735
<c.s0>They will not come back to help us, Angel.

20:37.737 --> 20:38.821
[ZONDI SIGHS]

20:38.905 --> 20:39.906
Angel?

20:40.907 --> 20:42.951
<c.s0>Gentlemen. I understand your position.

20:43.701 --> 20:44.869
<c.s0>But there's an election coming up,

20:44.953 --> 20:46.496
<c.s0>and Roman's name
is the only one on the ballot.

20:47.163 --> 20:48.998
<c.s0>No one will challenge him.

20:49.082 --> 20:51.918
We need to eliminate Roman's influence now

20:57.215 --> 20:58.549
[SIGHS]

21:01.302 --> 21:02.720
<c.s0>Why are you in Costa Verde?

21:08.059 --> 21:11.354
Angel, is there something else going on?

21:12.021 --> 21:14.232
Things here have escalated.

21:22.991 --> 21:26.786
<c.s0>So you will meet us
at the border with weapons, yes?

21:28.663 --> 21:29.747
<c.s0>We'll speak more then.

21:30.331 --> 21:33.292
<c.s0>But the clock is ticking.
We need to get moving.

21:33.376 --> 21:35.586
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

21:38.339 --> 21:39.465
BRANDON: <c.s0>I know it doesn't make sense

21:39.549 --> 21:41.217
<c.s0>that I'm not coming back
to Costa Verde to fight.

21:43.344 --> 21:44.554
<c.s0>Know that I'm with you.

21:54.689 --> 21:56.107
Staying was the right decision.

22:04.073 --> 22:05.658
<c.s0>at Kovalov's compound.

22:15.293 --> 22:17.253
ZONDI: <c.s0>I long to fight
by your side again, Brandon.

22:18.755 --> 22:19.756
<c.s0>Until that day,

22:20.923 --> 22:23.092
<c.s0>I'll continue to lead here on my own.

22:26.179 --> 22:27.346
<c.s0>Goodbye.

22:32.602 --> 22:35.229
Frost, I am sending you coordinates

22:35.313 --> 22:36.981
to the drop site.

22:37.065 --> 22:38.441
FROST: <c.s0>Standing by, Katrina.

22:40.651 --> 22:42.487
Why have we never done this before?

22:42.570 --> 22:44.489
Because I've seen you fight.

22:44.572 --> 22:46.282
Yeah, you're a little bit, um...

22:46.365 --> 22:47.533
Aggressive?

22:51.621 --> 22:53.247
[LAUGHS]

22:53.331 --> 22:54.332
All right.

22:55.750 --> 22:56.834
Show me what you got.

22:56.918 --> 22:58.127
[CLEARS THROAT]

23:02.507 --> 23:04.300
[GRUNTING]

23:04.967 --> 23:06.636
ZERO: Mm! [LAUGHS]

23:08.471 --> 23:10.098
[GRUNTING]

23:10.181 --> 23:11.349
[GROANS]

23:11.849 --> 23:14.685
[WHOOPING, LAUGHING]

23:18.106 --> 23:19.732
[BOTH GRUNTING]

23:22.026 --> 23:23.569
Oh, that was a good one.

23:27.865 --> 23:29.951
LORENZO: Commander Zondi.

23:30.034 --> 23:31.869
The Americans, will they join us?

23:37.333 --> 23:38.835
Our soldiers are ready.

23:48.636 --> 23:50.054
I will lead Alpha Squad.

23:50.721 --> 23:52.557
We need to be prepared for anything.

23:55.309 --> 23:56.310
We've gotta make sure that we're gonna--

23:58.146 --> 24:00.106
[EARS RINGING]

24:03.943 --> 24:06.112
[DRAMATIC ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

24:11.450 --> 24:13.911
Let's burn some ammo!

24:13.995 --> 24:15.538
[COUGHING]

24:40.229 --> 24:42.648
[DRAMATIC ROCK MUSIC CONTINUES]

24:48.738 --> 24:50.781
[WOMAN YELLS]

24:52.700 --> 24:53.868
[WOMAN GRUNTS]

24:54.535 --> 24:56.078
[GUNSHOTS]

24:57.705 --> 24:58.998
[GROANS]

25:00.625 --> 25:02.460
[GUNSHOTS]

25:09.008 --> 25:10.009
[GROANS]

25:10.885 --> 25:12.345
[GAGS]

25:34.116 --> 25:35.451
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

25:36.577 --> 25:38.120
[BOTH GRUNTING]

25:46.254 --> 25:48.673
[PANTING] Hey.

25:51.259 --> 25:52.343
Did we mess it up?

25:53.261 --> 25:54.553
The last assignment?

25:55.596 --> 25:56.806
Just look at the aftermath.

25:57.473 --> 26:01.394
People, like Stone, Intel Pete, Yuki,

26:01.477 --> 26:03.104
they're all on the run now and...

26:03.187 --> 26:05.022
We completed the assignment, B.

26:14.282 --> 26:15.449
We're gonna be home in no time.

26:18.286 --> 26:19.412
BRANDON: I don't know, man.

26:22.581 --> 26:23.416
[EXHALES]

26:35.553 --> 26:37.054
you just always have to leave again.

26:55.156 --> 26:57.616
Anyway, what are you gonna do?

26:58.617 --> 27:00.661
Job calls, we answer.

27:00.745 --> 27:02.246
Come on, let's go.

27:03.998 --> 27:04.915
[EXHALES]

27:04.999 --> 27:06.250
[TENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

27:06.334 --> 27:08.377
[WHIMPERING]

27:12.423 --> 27:14.425
[GUNSHOTS]

27:16.010 --> 27:17.845
[ARMOR CLANKING]

27:18.888 --> 27:20.181
[GUN CLICKS]

27:21.182 --> 27:22.892
[BOTH GRUNTING]

27:25.978 --> 27:26.979
[ANGEL GROANS]

27:28.314 --> 27:30.149
[ALL GRUNTING]

27:34.028 --> 27:35.071
[ZONDI GROANS]

27:36.155 --> 27:37.490
[ANGEL YELLING]

28:02.014 --> 28:03.015
[GROANS]

28:07.728 --> 28:09.980
[ZONDI GRUNTING]

28:27.665 --> 28:29.542
[ZONDI PANTING]

28:29.625 --> 28:30.626
Go!

28:34.964 --> 28:36.757
[GRUNTING]

28:38.175 --> 28:39.844
[GUNSHOT]

28:40.970 --> 28:42.304
[GRUNTING]

28:43.222 --> 28:44.473
[ZERO GROANS]

28:52.148 --> 28:53.315
Oh, shit. That was your wound.

28:53.399 --> 28:54.483
[GROANS]

28:54.567 --> 28:56.277
[GRUNTING]

29:00.698 --> 29:03.033
Come on, man! Not cool!

29:03.617 --> 29:05.202
I thought you were actually hurt.

29:13.335 --> 29:15.087
There's been an attack.

29:15.171 --> 29:17.047
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

29:18.090 --> 29:20.676
[GRUNTING AND BLOWS LANDING OVER VIDEO]

29:27.391 --> 29:29.310
[GUNFIRE]

29:32.897 --> 29:34.064
[ZONDI GROANS]

29:44.992 --> 29:46.827
[MUFFLED DISTANT GUNFIRE]

29:59.840 --> 30:01.342
<c.s0>Hope you enjoyed the show, Brandon.

30:05.137 --> 30:06.305
<c.s0>You're next.

30:11.227 --> 30:12.478
MAN: [OVER RADIO] <c.s0>Bridge secure.

30:13.354 --> 30:14.480
[KRUGER CLEARS THROAT]

30:22.196 --> 30:23.280
Otherwise, I'd cut you up

30:34.250 --> 30:35.251
"Whom."

30:38.128 --> 30:40.756
[ENUNCIATES] Whom. Who would cut whom.

30:48.138 --> 30:50.599
Body count is 50. So far.

30:52.101 --> 30:53.602
KRUGER: Ouch.

30:55.062 --> 30:56.438
Wanna know why?

30:57.940 --> 30:59.275
Brandon Beckett.

31:01.652 --> 31:04.405
Beckett wants you dead. All of you.

31:11.787 --> 31:13.956
we traced that call here.

31:21.755 --> 31:23.007
And he knew that.

31:24.508 --> 31:26.343
[DISQUIETING MUSIC PLAYING]

31:43.652 --> 31:44.945
[INHALES SHARPLY]

31:47.865 --> 31:49.658
I was hoping you'd say that.

31:51.076 --> 31:52.077
Legions!

31:52.161 --> 31:53.037
LEGIONS: Hoorah!

31:54.163 --> 31:55.164
Move out!

32:02.379 --> 32:03.547
[LAUGHTER]

32:04.381 --> 32:05.341
LEGION 2: I said move!

32:08.886 --> 32:12.014
FROST: <c.s0>I was on a video call with Katrina
when they hit.

32:12.848 --> 32:15.517
<c.s0>Over 50 Phoenix Rebels
were killed in the raid.

32:17.436 --> 32:19.688
Lorenzo, Angel, and Zondi.

32:19.772 --> 32:20.898
Holy shit.

32:25.986 --> 32:27.196
Who the hell are these guys?

32:29.490 --> 32:30.616
They're called the Iron Legion.

32:36.664 --> 32:38.832
These guys are the anti-G.R.I.T.

32:42.711 --> 32:44.421
from various places around the globe.

32:54.807 --> 32:56.809
turned hitman and anarchist.

33:05.734 --> 33:07.861
and mailing it to the Brigadier General.

33:18.831 --> 33:19.873
Francisco Cabrera,

33:25.754 --> 33:28.090
And finding you, Brandon.

33:35.723 --> 33:36.932
Us.

33:55.075 --> 33:56.660
So this is our fault.

34:00.164 --> 34:01.331
[SIGHS]

34:05.753 --> 34:06.754
FROST: We don't know.

34:15.971 --> 34:17.389
This is a trap.

34:17.473 --> 34:18.640
We don't have a choice.

34:22.144 --> 34:23.145
We have to find them!

34:29.318 --> 34:30.611
And they're coming here.

34:33.155 --> 34:34.573
When Katrina made it out,

34:46.251 --> 34:47.336
codenamed The Phoenix.

34:47.419 --> 34:49.379
If anyone discovers this weapon,

34:53.550 --> 34:56.053
So we're going into lockdown. Understand?

34:56.136 --> 34:58.138
[GRIPPING MUSIC PLAYING]

35:08.607 --> 35:10.067
[SEAGULLS SQUAWKING]

35:12.236 --> 35:14.571
KRUGER: Again, Prime Minister Díaz,

35:28.085 --> 35:29.962
Consider this place a loan.

35:30.045 --> 35:31.839
And if you continue to impress me,

35:44.017 --> 35:45.018
But...

35:47.771 --> 35:49.231
where is Brandon Beckett?

35:50.649 --> 35:53.944
I'll find him. But first, I have a gift.

36:02.744 --> 36:04.496
[ROMAN CHUCKLES]

36:06.373 --> 36:08.458
[IN ENGLISH] Put out a press release.

36:20.387 --> 36:23.515
and you will wipe them out in one swoop.

36:25.976 --> 36:28.395
But... and this is important...

36:29.521 --> 36:32.774
keep Brandon Beckett alive.

36:33.692 --> 36:35.235
I have plans for him.

36:35.319 --> 36:36.403
No problem.

36:47.372 --> 36:49.458
[WATER TRICKLING]

36:51.585 --> 36:53.587
KRUGER: Thabo Zondi.

36:54.963 --> 36:56.632
Hmm, we know all about you.

37:00.677 --> 37:02.429
when Daddy and Grandpa died in battle,

37:02.512 --> 37:03.889
because you went on and signed up

37:07.935 --> 37:11.229
Angel Anele.

37:12.064 --> 37:13.607
Former South African Police Services

37:18.320 --> 37:20.155
Lorenzo.

37:20.238 --> 37:22.532
You didn't partner up with G.R.I.T.,

37:28.163 --> 37:30.123
I mean, I don't have anything on you.

37:31.416 --> 37:32.459
There's no digital footprint.

38:09.454 --> 38:10.831
That's the best you've got?

38:11.540 --> 38:12.541
KRUGER: Nah, nah.

38:19.840 --> 38:21.258
I could kill your mother.

38:30.434 --> 38:32.144
Do they both have to die because of you?

38:34.646 --> 38:35.897
You won't break me.

38:36.982 --> 38:38.608
That's what they all say.

38:40.402 --> 38:41.737
You will talk, Zondi.

38:55.959 --> 38:57.586
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

39:08.930 --> 39:11.892
So, you're the Brandon Beckett.

39:12.350 --> 39:13.518
BRANDON: Guilty as charged.

39:14.019 --> 39:15.270
I've heard stories.

39:16.855 --> 39:18.690
I'm the Zero.

39:18.774 --> 39:20.317
We didn't catch your name.

39:20.400 --> 39:22.527
Oh. Skylar.

39:26.782 --> 39:28.784
How are your fiber optics here?

39:30.368 --> 39:32.162
Is that the weapon? Is that The Phoenix?

39:33.955 --> 39:36.166
No. That's a table.

39:45.342 --> 39:46.510
Be nice, Skylar.

39:48.011 --> 39:49.012
They're friends.

39:52.849 --> 39:53.850
BRANDON: Oh, shit.

39:56.269 --> 39:57.521
ZERO: You're alive.

39:59.564 --> 40:00.565
How?

40:02.609 --> 40:03.777
You're the asset.

40:12.702 --> 40:14.788
Spreading hope, brother.

40:17.165 --> 40:18.166
Brother?

40:18.250 --> 40:19.543
Oh, yeah. Skylar is my sister.

40:19.626 --> 40:21.837
Half. On our mother's side.

40:32.806 --> 40:34.766
Time is of the essence. Yeah?

40:44.901 --> 40:46.444
with only enough time for you

40:54.327 --> 40:56.288
Your lungs will fill up with water.

40:58.790 --> 41:00.292
You'll struggle to breathe.

41:01.418 --> 41:02.419
Your head will be on fire.

41:10.844 --> 41:12.888
Get it wrong,

41:12.971 --> 41:14.472
terminal hypoxia.

41:14.556 --> 41:16.892
[MUFFLED GROANING AND GAGGING]

41:17.684 --> 41:18.935
[GASPING]

41:19.019 --> 41:20.687
[WHIMPERING]

41:21.563 --> 41:22.856
Get it right...

41:23.690 --> 41:25.400
it's a slow, controlled death.

41:26.067 --> 41:27.944
[CHOKING]

41:30.614 --> 41:33.283
[GROANS, BREATHES HEAVILY]

41:33.992 --> 41:35.744
KRUGER: This is your last chance, Zondi.

41:36.912 --> 41:38.455
Angel.

41:38.538 --> 41:39.539
Lorenzo.

41:41.458 --> 41:42.626
Tell me.

41:42.709 --> 41:44.920
Tell me everything Beckett taught you.

41:46.463 --> 41:48.256
I need to know the Beckett playbook.

41:53.970 --> 41:55.013
[SNIFFS]

41:57.015 --> 41:58.016
Okay.

42:00.560 --> 42:01.561
Let's begin.

42:02.604 --> 42:03.813
[GROANS]

42:11.529 --> 42:13.240
That's led to a revolution.

42:18.703 --> 42:19.996
When my father was assassinated,

42:22.666 --> 42:24.376
Then after his death,

42:38.348 --> 42:39.933
Roman doesn't want to open the borders,

42:41.017 --> 42:42.644
because he wants to expand them

42:43.895 --> 42:46.982
into other countries... like Tierra Nueva.

42:47.065 --> 42:48.108
Mm-hmm.

42:49.150 --> 42:51.027
But for that to happen, he needs a war.

42:51.611 --> 42:52.612
NOVA: Exactly.

42:54.906 --> 42:56.032
SKYLAR: We're up and running.

42:57.867 --> 42:59.035
After my injuries,

43:03.373 --> 43:05.750
but I'm trying to do my best remotely.

43:15.593 --> 43:16.636
SKYLAR: You've got to be quick, though.

43:16.720 --> 43:18.305
Even with a signal relay,

43:24.144 --> 43:25.603
We learned that the hard way.

43:26.563 --> 43:27.689
What can we do, Nova?

43:33.445 --> 43:34.404
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

43:35.238 --> 43:36.323
Oh, bollocks.

43:39.909 --> 43:42.662
This just came in. Hang on.

43:45.040 --> 43:46.291
Let me translate it.

43:46.374 --> 43:48.376
[MONITOR CHIRRUPING]

43:53.256 --> 43:54.257
Executed?

44:00.138 --> 44:01.598
Anyone he deems a "terrorist"

44:05.018 --> 44:06.394
[SIGHS]

44:10.648 --> 44:11.691
How do we stop it?

44:24.287 --> 44:26.164
and it's impenetrable.

44:31.211 --> 44:32.837
without getting most of our people killed.

44:36.383 --> 44:38.760
We can't afford to lose anyone else.

44:41.679 --> 44:44.182
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

45:04.828 --> 45:06.121
[SIGHS SOFTLY]

45:20.844 --> 45:22.262
and respect your choice.

45:31.146 --> 45:32.230
Then I wish you good luck.

45:37.068 --> 45:38.236
Nova.

45:40.196 --> 45:41.739
It really is good to see you again.

45:45.869 --> 45:47.996
Thank you guys for letting us come here.

45:50.039 --> 45:51.040
But please,

46:14.272 --> 46:15.315
[BRANDON SIGHS]

46:16.274 --> 46:17.275
I don't know.

46:19.444 --> 46:20.278
[ZERO SIGHS]

46:22.572 --> 46:24.365
[WATER TRICKLING]

46:24.449 --> 46:26.451
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

46:28.661 --> 46:30.455
[CHAIR SCRAPING]

46:53.394 --> 46:55.104
But you know this, don't you?

46:56.689 --> 46:59.817
He led the Iron Legion right to you.

47:09.202 --> 47:11.329
but America is a pay-to-play country.

47:13.581 --> 47:18.211
I am making Costa Verde equal for all.

47:31.724 --> 47:33.351
and we can see how that turned out.

47:34.060 --> 47:35.812
The people, they don't want this.

47:36.980 --> 47:40.858
They want protection, security.

47:41.526 --> 47:44.070
And that is what I am providing.

47:45.280 --> 47:48.616
I am taking Costa Verde into the future,

48:01.671 --> 48:05.675
And I want you to be a part of it, son.

48:09.762 --> 48:14.851
But loyalty to Brandon Beckett

48:14.934 --> 48:17.186
comes with consequences.

48:22.275 --> 48:25.028
[BULLETS CLATTERING ON FLOOR]

48:28.740 --> 48:30.742
[BULLETS CONTINUE CLATTERING]

49:01.064 --> 49:02.398
[GUN CLICKS]

49:10.323 --> 49:11.366
ROMAN: What do you want, son?

49:12.283 --> 49:13.284
Hmm?

49:18.665 --> 49:20.291
ROMAN: I see potential in you.

49:44.065 --> 49:45.650
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

49:46.693 --> 49:48.444
ROMAN: You can be a leader, Zondi.

49:52.740 --> 49:54.826
[WATER TRICKLING ECHOES]

50:08.464 --> 50:10.466
ROMAN: Lead for me

50:10.550 --> 50:12.927
and I will make your legacy immortal.

50:37.994 --> 50:42.915
everything from this moment on...

50:44.917 --> 50:46.335
is a gift from me.

50:52.258 --> 50:53.760
I give you life.

50:55.344 --> 50:57.430
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

51:02.310 --> 51:03.978
It's morphine.

51:04.061 --> 51:06.147
I am here to help you, son.

51:07.857 --> 51:09.942
[GASPING HOARSELY]

51:15.114 --> 51:17.116
[BREATHING SLOWS]

51:27.668 --> 51:30.880
THE STAR-SPANGLED BANNER

51:40.139 --> 51:41.557
[ZERO EXHALES HEAVILY]

51:49.273 --> 51:51.734
It's okay. I'm done anyway.

51:53.486 --> 51:55.905
Yeah. I can't believe you're alive, Nova.

51:55.988 --> 51:58.366
I'm so thankful, man. We didn't know.

52:08.000 --> 52:11.170
Holy shit. Look at you.

52:15.424 --> 52:16.425
I just came to get some aspirin.

52:25.476 --> 52:27.645
Brandon and I can't give up.

52:27.728 --> 52:29.480
Lost our G.R.I.T. team.

52:31.524 --> 52:32.984
Lost so many others.

52:38.072 --> 52:40.741
Funny about the G.R.I.T. team.

52:43.035 --> 52:45.037
All this time we spent together,

52:50.167 --> 52:53.588
about Yuki Mifune being part of your team.

53:02.513 --> 53:03.514
Well,

53:05.725 --> 53:06.851
nobody's perfect.

53:09.353 --> 53:11.564
Look, Nova, we're all grunts here.

53:13.482 --> 53:15.276
I promise you, it is not personal.

53:17.153 --> 53:18.154
Not personal?

53:26.287 --> 53:27.288
Yeah.

53:39.842 --> 53:40.927
Zero...

53:44.096 --> 53:47.600
in every assignment, you've gone in,

53:47.683 --> 53:51.228
saved the day, and walk away.

54:04.492 --> 54:08.955
This Lady Death in your team, Yuki,

54:15.503 --> 54:16.504
[TUTS SOFTLY]

54:22.426 --> 54:24.053
Have you ever contemplated that?

54:27.348 --> 54:28.474
[ZERO SIGHS]

54:34.981 --> 54:40.027
I already died once for this cause.

54:42.279 --> 54:43.698
And it changed me.

54:59.630 --> 55:00.840
No, hold on. Listen to me.

55:05.261 --> 55:08.264
[SCOFFING] They don't! No!

55:38.586 --> 55:39.670
Goodnight, Zero.

55:46.260 --> 55:47.261
[SNIFFS]

55:50.973 --> 55:52.600
[WIND HOWLING]

55:54.101 --> 55:55.811
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

55:56.729 --> 55:57.897
[DOOR SHUTS]

56:01.233 --> 56:02.860
[GROANING SOFTLY]

56:06.614 --> 56:07.615
Zondi?

56:13.704 --> 56:14.705
Zondi!

56:17.917 --> 56:19.585
[IN XHOSA] I'm here with you.

56:26.759 --> 56:28.302
How?

56:30.763 --> 56:32.098
[IN ENGLISH] No one is coming for us.

56:32.181 --> 56:34.266
ANGEL: No. That's not true.

56:34.350 --> 56:36.185
The Rebellion would never leave us.

56:52.368 --> 56:53.536
Have you forgotten that?

56:53.619 --> 56:54.995
Then they turned their backs on us.

56:57.581 --> 56:58.874
They left us, Angel.

57:06.590 --> 57:08.008
they abandoned us again.

57:09.635 --> 57:11.137
Which put us in here.

57:11.220 --> 57:13.222
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

57:19.562 --> 57:20.688
Even without a country,

57:25.109 --> 57:26.110
He's weak.

57:27.695 --> 57:29.363
This was never our battle.

57:35.161 --> 57:36.579
But, brother, I promise you--

57:36.662 --> 57:38.664
I don't need your sympathy.

57:57.141 --> 57:59.977
INTEL PETE: [OVER PHONE] <c.s0>These blueprints
and schematics are the best I could find.

58:00.060 --> 58:02.354
<c.s0>They break down the detention center
from every level,

58:02.438 --> 58:04.815
<c.s0>but I honestly don't see a weak spot.

58:04.899 --> 58:07.318
<c.s0>But hey, you're the Marine, not me.

58:07.401 --> 58:09.153
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

58:09.778 --> 58:11.947
Thanks, Pete. These are great.

58:12.865 --> 58:13.949
<c.s0>What else can I do?

58:14.033 --> 58:17.369
<c.s0>There's gotta be something.
I mean, those people were killed when I--

58:21.832 --> 58:22.875
There's no way we could've known

58:27.463 --> 58:29.715
The Legion took those lives.

58:29.798 --> 58:32.801
Those deaths are on them. Not you.

58:32.885 --> 58:35.221
<c.s0>Whoever traced that signal
was a pro, Brandon.

58:35.304 --> 58:36.764
<c.s0>Like, a coding savant.

58:36.847 --> 58:39.141
<c.s0>I've never seen anything like it.

58:39.225 --> 58:41.060
<c.s0>Be careful. Okay?

58:41.143 --> 58:42.311
[SIGHS]

58:42.394 --> 58:45.022
We will. Thanks for the blueprints.

58:45.105 --> 58:46.106
<c.s0>Sorry, man.

58:54.573 --> 58:55.950
Guy's changed.

58:58.369 --> 59:00.454
Well, four bullets will do that to you.

59:08.003 --> 59:09.004
He has a point.

59:11.131 --> 59:12.299
You do this job

59:19.139 --> 59:20.808
That is very eloquent.

59:23.477 --> 59:24.770
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

59:25.729 --> 59:27.898
'Cause I was here.

59:34.488 --> 59:36.031
I can't see a way to breach.

59:37.199 --> 59:39.368
I mean, the sewer tunnels are a no-go.

59:39.451 --> 59:41.161
It's too risky to drop in from above.

59:45.666 --> 59:46.667
[SIGHS]

59:48.711 --> 59:49.712
Nova might be right.

59:52.548 --> 59:54.091
We can't give up, though, B.

59:54.174 --> 59:55.509
They're not going out this way.

59:57.261 --> 59:59.471
We still have a few hours.

59:59.555 --> 01:00:00.556
Okay.

01:00:02.516 --> 01:00:03.642
Let's try this again.

01:00:05.853 --> 01:00:07.688
These are the blueprints IP sent you.

01:00:08.397 --> 01:00:10.482
[BRANDON EXHALES HEAVILY]

01:00:10.566 --> 01:00:13.944
What if we grab one of those old trucks,

01:00:18.115 --> 01:00:19.700
Well, that's what they expect us to do.

01:00:20.784 --> 01:00:23.162
Charge in, guns blazing.

01:00:24.038 --> 01:00:25.914
But we cannot do that, just the two of us.

01:00:28.500 --> 01:00:29.501
BRANDON: Nah.

01:00:38.510 --> 01:00:40.346
You just reminded me of it.

01:00:49.021 --> 01:00:50.022
So, what'd you do?

01:00:51.607 --> 01:00:52.691
Well, your father said,

01:00:57.863 --> 01:00:59.031
[BRANDON SIGHS]

01:01:02.409 --> 01:01:03.535
That's the answer.

01:01:03.619 --> 01:01:04.953
ZERO: Mm.

01:01:06.163 --> 01:01:07.164
Wait, what?

01:01:11.293 --> 01:01:13.170
We don't hit the detention center.

01:01:27.434 --> 01:01:28.435
That could work.

01:01:32.731 --> 01:01:34.441
in the middle of town,

01:01:40.030 --> 01:01:42.533
as long as we can get that convoy here.

01:01:44.535 --> 01:01:46.036
We create a kill box.

01:01:50.874 --> 01:01:53.419
My brother and I can direct them there.

01:01:53.502 --> 01:01:55.379
We'll get into their GPS system.

01:01:57.631 --> 01:02:00.008
With my eyes closed.

01:02:00.092 --> 01:02:03.345
We can help, Nova. From here.

01:02:04.012 --> 01:02:05.013
[SIGHS]

01:02:11.061 --> 01:02:12.354
All right.

01:02:18.402 --> 01:02:19.736
Thank you.

01:02:19.820 --> 01:02:22.281
[ROUSING MUSIC PLAYING]

01:02:29.455 --> 01:02:31.415
We've faced worse odds.

01:02:31.498 --> 01:02:33.292
Plus this time, we've got some backup.

01:02:34.126 --> 01:02:35.669
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

01:02:39.173 --> 01:02:40.632
SKYLAR: This is your backup?

01:02:47.473 --> 01:02:48.849
[SKYLAR SCOFFS]

01:02:49.683 --> 01:02:50.976
So there's only three of you.

01:02:52.060 --> 01:02:54.730
Three's enough. One shot, one kill.

01:02:55.772 --> 01:02:56.773
One shot, one kill.

01:02:57.483 --> 01:02:59.276
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

01:02:59.860 --> 01:03:03.030
ZERO: <c.s0>At the kill box,
Brandon and Thomas

01:03:03.113 --> 01:03:04.281
<c.s0>-will be overwatch.

01:03:05.782 --> 01:03:08.243
<c.s0>We need you on the same team.

01:03:08.327 --> 01:03:10.078
Well, hello, old friend.

01:03:14.875 --> 01:03:17.669
ZERO: <c.s0>I'll be in charge
of evac'ing the hostages.

01:03:17.753 --> 01:03:19.087
Even with armor-piercing rounds,

01:03:25.928 --> 01:03:27.012
You look for the seams.

01:03:30.516 --> 01:03:33.519
BRANDON: <c.s0>Nova and Skylar,
you are our eyes and ears.

01:03:33.602 --> 01:03:36.605
<c.s0>So make sure Cinderella gets to the ball.

01:03:45.197 --> 01:03:48.659
BRANDON: <c.s0>And Frost, you're on extraction.
We'll be coming in hot.

01:03:48.742 --> 01:03:50.118
Maybe it's time to upgrade.

01:04:03.257 --> 01:04:06.301
We need to be ready. Let's load up.

01:04:13.016 --> 01:04:16.478
I'm glad you're here. Both of you.

01:04:34.037 --> 01:04:35.455
[WATER TRICKLING]

01:05:00.147 --> 01:05:01.356
Dragged?

01:05:18.332 --> 01:05:21.043
I guess that's the curse of Costa Verde.

01:05:27.549 --> 01:05:29.968
I only did one tour of duty down here.

01:05:39.186 --> 01:05:42.898
he had all of us write our own obituaries.

01:05:44.775 --> 01:05:47.778
Yeah. What a piece of work he was. Whoa.

01:05:48.737 --> 01:05:49.738
[CHUCKLES]

01:05:50.364 --> 01:05:52.699
I guess he figured that, uh...

01:05:53.825 --> 01:05:55.077
[CLEARS THROAT]

01:06:01.750 --> 01:06:02.751
[CHUCKLES DRYLY]

01:06:03.794 --> 01:06:05.629
Death? [SCOFFS] Shit!

01:06:06.463 --> 01:06:07.464
[SPITS]

01:06:08.465 --> 01:06:10.092
I spit on death.

01:06:17.224 --> 01:06:19.059
But you know what I did fear?

01:06:23.939 --> 01:06:28.735
I feared that I might never see you again.

01:06:32.698 --> 01:06:33.949
I was...

01:06:35.617 --> 01:06:37.452
I was never present enough.

01:06:38.412 --> 01:06:40.205
Just not there.

01:06:52.426 --> 01:06:54.344
I'm sorry.

01:06:56.304 --> 01:06:57.472
[SIGHS]

01:07:04.688 --> 01:07:06.606
did any of it really matter?

01:07:09.985 --> 01:07:13.405
Did anything I ever do change things?

01:07:14.489 --> 01:07:16.074
I don't know.

01:07:18.577 --> 01:07:20.579
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

01:07:21.329 --> 01:07:22.706
I don't know that... that...

01:07:25.625 --> 01:07:28.086
Hey. It did.

01:07:40.015 --> 01:07:41.224
[CLEARS THROAT]

01:07:55.781 --> 01:07:57.032
Ah, mmm.

01:08:00.786 --> 01:08:01.828
Mr. Rosenberg?

01:08:02.913 --> 01:08:05.791
Hey, Katrina. Hey. You can call me Zero.

01:08:14.549 --> 01:08:16.343
And it is not my place to argue.

01:08:16.426 --> 01:08:18.261
But there has to be something I can do.

01:08:30.190 --> 01:08:31.191
[SIGHS]

01:08:32.025 --> 01:08:34.820
[IN SPANISH] May fate be in your favor.

01:08:35.487 --> 01:08:36.696
Thank you.

01:08:41.785 --> 01:08:43.495
[BRANDON EXHALES HEAVILY]

01:08:46.706 --> 01:08:50.418
We're not old. We're experienced.

01:08:50.502 --> 01:08:51.503
Ha!

01:09:02.764 --> 01:09:04.057
Look at how I left him.

01:09:05.517 --> 01:09:07.602
I can't get Angel's words out of my head.

01:09:09.312 --> 01:09:10.772
I should have stayed longer.

01:09:15.360 --> 01:09:16.528
He's just a kid, man.

01:09:17.404 --> 01:09:19.030
With Modise gone...

01:09:21.491 --> 01:09:22.576
You know, I get it now.

01:09:23.410 --> 01:09:25.036
We finish an assignment and head home,

01:09:31.877 --> 01:09:33.420
Yeah.

01:09:35.672 --> 01:09:37.424
or what we've been doing for years, B.

01:09:38.758 --> 01:09:40.176
Because we have a job to do.

01:09:42.429 --> 01:09:43.430
Okay?

01:09:44.222 --> 01:09:45.056
[PATS]

01:09:49.102 --> 01:09:50.812
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

01:10:00.780 --> 01:10:02.866
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

01:10:14.794 --> 01:10:16.046
Seatbelts!

01:10:19.925 --> 01:10:21.593
[QUINN CHUCKLING]

01:10:32.896 --> 01:10:35.023
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

01:10:55.669 --> 01:10:57.379
Let's get into their GPS.

01:11:05.470 --> 01:11:07.472
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

01:11:16.898 --> 01:11:18.358
There you are.

01:11:28.118 --> 01:11:29.327
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

01:11:47.637 --> 01:11:49.723
[GRIPPING MUSIC PLAYING]

01:12:14.998 --> 01:12:16.875
This way, you wanker.

01:12:25.925 --> 01:12:27.761
No, don't question it.

01:12:32.223 --> 01:12:33.850
'Cause I need you to go...

01:12:36.561 --> 01:12:37.562
right.

01:12:37.645 --> 01:12:38.980
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

01:12:39.064 --> 01:12:40.315
GPS: <c.s0>Turn right.

01:12:45.904 --> 01:12:47.989
[GRIPPING MUSIC CONTINUES]

01:12:52.160 --> 01:12:53.787
<c.s0>Turn left.

01:13:27.654 --> 01:13:28.696
[OVER COMMS] <c.s0>Thirty seconds.

01:13:36.162 --> 01:13:38.540
[OVER COMMS] <c.s0>Overwatch Two.
You've got the armored truck.

01:13:39.958 --> 01:13:42.043
Overwatch Two in position.

01:13:42.127 --> 01:13:44.462
Zero, you're on the last vehicle.

01:13:44.546 --> 01:13:46.756
In position. Let's get to work.

01:13:55.223 --> 01:13:56.474
Convoy has arrived.

01:13:57.600 --> 01:13:59.269
<c.s0>Overwatch One, make the call.

01:13:59.352 --> 01:14:01.437
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:14:06.818 --> 01:14:07.902
Overwatch One here.

01:14:08.987 --> 01:14:12.031
Overwatch Two, on my count.

01:14:15.410 --> 01:14:16.578
Something's off.

01:14:16.661 --> 01:14:21.457
Green light in three... two... one. Fire!

01:14:22.834 --> 01:14:23.751
[DRIVER GRUNTS]

01:14:36.014 --> 01:14:37.015
MAN: Oh, shi--

01:14:42.520 --> 01:14:44.439
[ALL BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:14:45.732 --> 01:14:46.566
ZERO: Contact made!

01:14:46.649 --> 01:14:48.484
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

01:14:48.568 --> 01:14:50.778
KRUGER: Everybody out! Covering fire!

01:14:52.113 --> 01:14:53.781
[GUNFIRE]

01:14:53.865 --> 01:14:56.159
Out, out, out! Everybody out!

01:15:00.330 --> 01:15:01.748
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

01:15:11.507 --> 01:15:13.301
[BULLETS RICOCHETING]

01:15:18.723 --> 01:15:20.850
Up here, asshole! Look this way.

01:15:31.903 --> 01:15:33.029
[GUN FIRES]

01:15:35.240 --> 01:15:36.449
[QUINN GRUNTS]

01:15:39.160 --> 01:15:41.246
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

01:15:51.965 --> 01:15:55.093
Beckett! Where are you?

01:16:04.060 --> 01:16:06.104
CABRERA: [OVER PHONE] <c.s0>You're late, Kruger!
What the hell is going on?

01:16:09.107 --> 01:16:12.610
<c.s0>Handle it! You're the Iron fucking Legion!
This is what we're paying you for!

01:16:16.572 --> 01:16:18.324
<c.s0>I don't even know where you are!

01:16:20.576 --> 01:16:21.828
[IN AFRIKAANS] Fucking dumbass!

01:16:34.716 --> 01:16:35.717
LEGION: [IN ENGLISH] Watch my six!

01:16:35.800 --> 01:16:37.051
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

01:16:37.719 --> 01:16:39.220
[GUNFIRE CONTINUES]

01:16:48.855 --> 01:16:50.815
Everybody out, now!

01:16:51.566 --> 01:16:52.900
Yayan, on me!

01:17:02.910 --> 01:17:08.166
Vince, move! Now!

01:17:08.249 --> 01:17:09.625
THOMAS: [SOFTLY] Come on.

01:17:11.210 --> 01:17:12.420
[GRUNTS]

01:17:15.006 --> 01:17:16.090
Son of a--

01:17:16.174 --> 01:17:18.384
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:17:23.348 --> 01:17:25.058
[ALL GRUNTING]

01:17:43.326 --> 01:17:44.786
[CHOKING]

01:18:07.850 --> 01:18:08.851
Move!

01:18:19.654 --> 01:18:20.655
[EXCLAIMS]

01:18:28.913 --> 01:18:30.415
[GRUNTING]

01:18:30.498 --> 01:18:31.457
[ANGEL YELPS]

01:18:33.000 --> 01:18:34.669
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:18:39.507 --> 01:18:40.925
[ANGEL SCREAMS]

01:18:41.008 --> 01:18:42.844
[BOTH STRAINING]

01:18:57.775 --> 01:18:59.235
[PANTING]

01:19:05.366 --> 01:19:06.492
ZERO: [SOFTLY] Shit!

01:19:07.910 --> 01:19:09.537
[GUNFIRE CONTINUES]

01:19:18.713 --> 01:19:20.339
[OVER COMMS] <c.s0>I'm pinned down.

01:19:20.423 --> 01:19:21.424
BRANDON: I'm on it.

01:19:21.507 --> 01:19:23.968
[GRIPPING ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

01:19:28.556 --> 01:19:29.557
[GROANS]

01:19:33.895 --> 01:19:35.354
KRUGER: Move!

01:19:40.109 --> 01:19:42.320
ZERO: Fuck me! [SIGHS]

01:19:58.252 --> 01:19:59.337
SKYLAR: <c.s0>Copy. On it.

01:20:00.546 --> 01:20:02.757
ZERO: <c.s0>Find Angel.
She's still in the mix somewhere.

01:20:14.644 --> 01:20:17.396
Overwatch One, leaving position.

01:20:17.480 --> 01:20:19.732
ZERO: Copy. I'm going after Lorenzo.

01:20:21.317 --> 01:20:23.319
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

01:20:47.510 --> 01:20:49.262
[GUN COCKING]

01:20:50.763 --> 01:20:51.764
ANGEL: [SOFTLY] Fuck!

01:20:59.897 --> 01:21:01.524
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:21:11.492 --> 01:21:13.703
Damn it! I don't have a clean shot.

01:21:13.786 --> 01:21:15.496
[PANTING]

01:21:23.212 --> 01:21:25.506
I got this. Evac.

01:21:25.590 --> 01:21:28.175
Roger that. Heading to Frost.

01:21:31.929 --> 01:21:34.390
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:21:35.850 --> 01:21:37.226
[LORENZO BREATHING SHAKILY]

01:21:37.310 --> 01:21:38.728
It's not a fuckin' game.

01:21:41.230 --> 01:21:42.648
[GRUNTING]

01:21:50.281 --> 01:21:52.074
[LORENZO COUGHS]

01:21:56.996 --> 01:21:58.289
[CONTINUES GASPING]

01:21:59.957 --> 01:22:01.500
[ZERO YELLS]

01:22:01.584 --> 01:22:02.752
[KRUGER GRUNTS]

01:22:09.842 --> 01:22:11.552
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:22:16.974 --> 01:22:18.768
Ezekiel Rosenberg.

01:22:19.685 --> 01:22:20.936
I've heard about you.

01:22:22.563 --> 01:22:24.732
You're Beckett's little side-bitch, huh?

01:22:28.277 --> 01:22:29.737
It's Zero, motherfucker.

01:22:31.739 --> 01:22:33.491
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:22:47.463 --> 01:22:48.964
[STRAINING]

01:22:50.049 --> 01:22:51.258
[CHOKES]

01:22:59.350 --> 01:23:00.935
[BOTH PANTING]

01:23:06.649 --> 01:23:08.818
[PANTING, CHUCKLING]

01:23:11.862 --> 01:23:13.864
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:23:23.541 --> 01:23:25.084
[BOTH STRAINING]

01:23:36.971 --> 01:23:38.973
[QUINN SCREAMS]

01:23:41.517 --> 01:23:43.269
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:23:45.438 --> 01:23:46.856
[GROANS]

01:23:55.197 --> 01:23:56.532
[GROANS]

01:23:58.242 --> 01:24:00.286
[BRANDON PANTING]

01:24:02.997 --> 01:24:04.874
[GROANING]

01:24:04.957 --> 01:24:06.959
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

01:24:12.047 --> 01:24:12.882
[SPITS]

01:24:13.466 --> 01:24:14.842
[GRUNTING]

01:24:17.803 --> 01:24:18.637
[CHUCKLES]

01:24:20.514 --> 01:24:22.516
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:24:33.027 --> 01:24:34.320
[ZERO YELLS]

01:24:35.529 --> 01:24:37.364
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:24:44.872 --> 01:24:46.874
[GASPING]

01:24:57.259 --> 01:24:58.385
[GROANING]

01:24:58.469 --> 01:24:59.720
Kruger's down.

01:25:00.638 --> 01:25:02.890
Ah. I've got Angel and Lorenzo with me.

01:25:03.682 --> 01:25:05.017
Free and clear.

01:25:05.100 --> 01:25:08.687
BRANDON: <c.s0>You need to get out of there.
Get the chopper ready for dust off.

01:25:11.857 --> 01:25:13.275
CVPD is swarming the area. It's--

01:25:13.359 --> 01:25:14.527
[RADIO STATIC WHINES]

01:25:14.610 --> 01:25:15.611
Hello?

01:25:16.695 --> 01:25:19.073
Nova, can you see a clear way out?

01:25:19.657 --> 01:25:21.158
[RADIO STATIC]

01:25:21.242 --> 01:25:22.326
Nova?

01:25:22.409 --> 01:25:23.911
[RADIO STATIC]

01:25:23.994 --> 01:25:24.995
Zero, come in.

01:25:25.079 --> 01:25:27.164
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

01:25:41.679 --> 01:25:42.888
[HORN HONKS]

01:25:59.572 --> 01:26:00.573
ZERO: Frost!

01:26:01.365 --> 01:26:02.408
FROST: It's about time.

01:26:04.660 --> 01:26:06.078
Where's Zondi and the Becketts?

01:26:07.705 --> 01:26:08.956
Wait, they should be here.

01:26:14.837 --> 01:26:16.422
[RADIO STATIC]

01:26:18.632 --> 01:26:20.801
Nova? Skylar? Do you copy?

01:26:20.885 --> 01:26:22.636
[RADIO STATIC]

01:26:24.471 --> 01:26:27.516
Shit! Comms are down.

01:26:30.311 --> 01:26:32.354
Zondi, we good?

01:26:32.938 --> 01:26:34.356
ZONDI: All good.

01:26:35.900 --> 01:26:38.152
Our evac's on the south side of town.

01:26:51.457 --> 01:26:53.459
[RADIO STATIC CRACKLING]

01:26:54.168 --> 01:26:55.753
Who the bloody hell was that?

01:27:04.553 --> 01:27:05.679
What the f--

01:27:25.074 --> 01:27:27.284
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:27:31.705 --> 01:27:32.831
BRANDON: Zondi, what are you doing?

01:27:34.166 --> 01:27:35.668
What the hell is going on?

01:27:40.130 --> 01:27:41.507
I risked everything for you!

01:27:41.590 --> 01:27:42.841
ZONDI: You're too late.

01:27:43.926 --> 01:27:45.010
[SOFTLY] Fuck!

01:27:45.094 --> 01:27:46.303
Jesus.

01:27:46.387 --> 01:27:48.472
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

01:27:54.186 --> 01:27:56.689
Fuck. It's that fucking <c.s0>cabrón,

01:27:57.272 --> 01:27:59.358
Damn it. I've only got one shot left.

01:27:59.441 --> 01:28:01.151
How fast can you hot wire this car?

01:28:03.195 --> 01:28:04.697
We aren't gonna win this one, son.

01:28:05.239 --> 01:28:07.491
Give me. Give me!

01:28:16.291 --> 01:28:17.668
Go, Brandon.

01:28:19.420 --> 01:28:20.421
Go!

01:28:34.226 --> 01:28:36.228
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:28:45.320 --> 01:28:46.405
Brandon...

01:28:49.158 --> 01:28:51.160
I just want you to know something.

01:29:01.920 --> 01:29:03.047
<c.s0>semper fi,

01:29:04.131 --> 01:29:05.132
[GUN FIRES]

01:29:07.301 --> 01:29:08.510
[GUN FIRES]

01:29:12.389 --> 01:29:14.099
[GRUNTS]

01:29:17.186 --> 01:29:18.187
ROMAN: Don't shoot!

01:29:24.693 --> 01:29:26.695
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

01:29:31.575 --> 01:29:33.619
[MUSIC BUILDING]

01:29:34.828 --> 01:29:35.913
[GUN COCKS]

01:29:37.498 --> 01:29:38.874
[GUNSHOT ECHOES]

01:29:38.957 --> 01:29:41.293
BRANDON: [SCREAMS] No!

01:29:44.713 --> 01:29:46.715
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

01:29:56.058 --> 01:29:58.268
[WATER TRICKLING]

01:29:58.352 --> 01:30:00.354
[DOOR CREAKS, CLOSES HEAVILY]

01:30:01.855 --> 01:30:02.898
[SWITCH CLACKS]

01:30:07.611 --> 01:30:08.612
Hello, Brandon.

01:30:16.829 --> 01:30:18.163
[GRUNTS]

01:30:18.247 --> 01:30:19.331
[GROWLS]

01:30:20.624 --> 01:30:22.209
You set us up, you traitor!

01:30:30.759 --> 01:30:32.845
These ropes won't hold me forever.

01:30:34.221 --> 01:30:35.806
I will be free.

01:30:35.889 --> 01:30:36.974
And when I am,

01:30:38.517 --> 01:30:40.352
I will end you, Thabo Zondi.

01:30:41.311 --> 01:30:43.063
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:30:43.147 --> 01:30:44.231
[GUNSHOTS]

01:30:49.528 --> 01:30:50.779
<c.s0>This is my vengeance!

01:30:51.321 --> 01:30:53.157
[GRUNTING]

01:30:53.240 --> 01:30:54.324
[EXPLOSION]

01:30:54.992 --> 01:30:57.035
<c.s0>-Take the goddamn shot!

01:30:57.119 --> 01:30:58.912
ZONDI: <c.s0>Your legacy ends here.

01:30:58.996 --> 01:31:00.372
[GUN FIRES]

01:31:00.455 --> 01:31:02.583
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

01:31:05.085 --> 01:31:07.504
[GRIPPING TRAP MUSIC PLAYING]

01:32:02.476 --> 01:32:04.895
[UPBEAT ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYING]

01:33:19.845 --> 01:33:22.264
[DRAMATIC ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYING]
